15 . Dynamic components //Hello.jsx file how to make dynamic

//basic coding 

Hello.jsx

function Hello(){

  let myName = 'Prashant'
  return <h3>
    Hello this is the future speaking. I am your master {myName}
  </h3>
}

export default Hello;

<Hello this is the future speaking. I am your master Prashant

*************************************************
//add more content on it

Hello.jsx
function Hello(){

  let myName = 'Prashant';
  let fullName = () =>{
    return 'Prashant Jain';
  }

  return <h3>
    Hello this is the future speaking. I am your master {fullName()}
  </h3>
}

export default Hello;

<This is a best react course
Hello this is the future speaking. I am your master Prashant Jain

***********************************
//for dynamic more thing include like number

function Hello(){

  let myName = 'Prashant';
  let number = 456;
  let fullName = () =>{
    return 'Prashant Jain';
  }

  return <p>
    MessageNo: {number} I am your master {fullName()}
  </p>
}

export default Hello;

<MessageNo: 456 I am your master Prashant Jain

15. Dynamic Components
 1. Dynamic Content: JSX allows the 
creation of dynamic and interactive 
UI components.
 2. JavaScript Expressions: Using {}, we 
can embed any JS expression 
directly within JSX. This includes 
variables, function calls, and more.


